type(scope): subject (≤50 chars, imperative, no period)

# Body starts after the blank line. For docs/test/ci/refactor the body is optional,
# but recommended for non-trivial changes. Keep lines ~72 chars when possible.

Why:
- What problem does this change solve? Why now? (1–2 lines)

How:
- What changed at a high level? Mention key files/modules (1–3 lines)

Validation:
- How did you verify it? CI/tests/links resolve/behavior checked (1–3 lines)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Allowed types (per commit-msg hook):
#   mm, alloc, lock, feat, fix, perf, refactor, test, docs, ci
#
# Allowed scopes (per commit-msg hook):
#   buddy, slab, manager, arena, freelist, gc, os, sync, api, align,
#   ring, zerocopy, watchdog, telemetry, ecs, timestep, simd, hal, loop,
#   roadmap, readme, release, adr, repro, bench, workflow, hook, changelog
#
# Examples:
#   docs(roadmap): finalize v0.1.0–v0.3.0
#   ci(workflow): align steps with README Quick Start
#   test(slab): add alignment floor cases for sizeof(void*)
#
# Notes:
# - Subject must NOT end with a period.
# - Keep second line blank.
# - Required body for types: mm, alloc, lock, feat, fix, perf.
# - Body optional for: docs, test, ci, refactor (still recommended).